description.narrative: The specific objective of this project is to support programs designed to halt transmission of HIV/AIDS among vulnerable populations( PLWHA, IDUs, CSWs, and their clients and sexual partners) and between these vulnerable populations and the general population. Key outcome indicators include: ** Percent of vulnerable groups in participating provinces reporting safer injection practices (from an estimated 20% at baseline to 70% at the project end ) ** Percent of vulnerable groups in participating provinces reporting condom use in sexual intercourse (from an estimated 40% at baseline to 80% at project end)

condition.narrative: Adopt a national HIV/AIDS Monitoring and Evaluation Plan acceptable to IDA
By October 31 each year, starting in 2005, each participating province and city shall prepare and submit to the CPMU an annualProvincial HIV/AIDS Action Plan
By October 31 each year, starting in 2006, prepare and provide to IDA for review and comments an annual implementation plan
Establish a National Monitoring and Evaluation Unit within the Dept. of HIV/AIDS Control in MOH
Establish regional Monitoring and Evaluation Centers in NIHE in Hanoi, Pasteur Inst. in HCMC, Pasteur Inst. in Nha Trang andHygiene & Epidemiology Inst. of the Highland in Dak Lak Province
Establish the Technical Review Team to assist the CPMU and Provincial AIDS Steering Committee
Prepare, under TORs acceptable to IDA, and submit to IDA a report on the results of montoring & evaluation activities, progressandrecommendations in carrying out the Project.
